On September 10, 2013, eight additional countries - Georgia, Guatemala, Kuwait, Malta, Montenegro, Panama, Poland, and Portugal - signed on to a joint statement condemning the Assad regime's use of chemical weapons in Syria on August 21. The statement also expresses support for international efforts to prohibit the use of chemical weapons. With these additions, a total of 33 countries now formally support this statement. The White House welcomes the support from these countries and continues its efforts to hold the Assad regime accountable for its actions. The full list of supporting countries can be found at http://obamawhitehouse.archives.gov/issues/foreign-policy/syria.